the acceptance of Evangelicalism. Evangelicalism is a new doctrine. It is a new way to understand the Bible, to connect with God through prayer, and also to change the way we act with the people. Actually, it was a new way to understand religion. According to a survey last year, 90% Salvadoran understand that the phrases in the Bible were spoken by Jesus and 85% said that they are supposed to follow Jesus' commandments.

The majority of youth make their faith personally, they don't read or listen even sing a song in church only a church-related, mostly some of the songs have to do with politics, like the song of Ezekiel by Theophany and Grupo MIR has the song EDEN that refers to the garden of Eden by Genesis. There is a faith shift going on in our country, more people are interested in God because something is absent in their lives. According to the survey, if you ask 100 Salvadorans who know about Jesus Christ, 50% says he was a human who practiced the word of God.

Salvadoran's are leaving their religion because many of them can't find the answers to life. The fact that we lost our heritage Cuscatlana (Traditional Identities) makes us feel like we don't have a purpose in this life and even those who are baptized feel that they are empty because the doctrines they were taught are not real.
